00:00:14.048 --> 00:00:18.208
How do we learn to recognize when God is speaking to us?

00:00:18.240 --> 00:00:20.544
On the morning of the resurrection,

00:00:20.576 --> 00:00:23.904
Mary Magdalene didn't recognize Jesus.

00:00:23.584 --> 00:00:26.432
And she thought he was merely the gardener.

00:00:26.400 --> 00:00:30.144
Because the Bible says his grave was located

00:00:29.952 --> 00:00:31.232
In a garden.

00:00:31.552 --> 00:00:36.896
But the moment Jesus spoke to her, Mary instantly recognized his voice.

00:00:37.280 --> 00:00:40.224
And it was a transforming moment in her life.

00:00:40.096 --> 00:00:43.104
Because Jesus had been raised from the dead.

00:00:43.488 --> 00:00:45.408
And he would call her.

00:00:45.216 --> 00:00:48.032
To announce to his disciples

00:00:47.904 --> 00:00:50.240
that Jesus is alive.

00:00:50.208 --> 00:00:58.144
And today I want to share with you how you can better hear and discern that still small voice of God in your heart.

00:00:57.888 --> 00:00:59.232
In your life.

00:01:15.008 --> 00:01:19.744
Hello, I'm Christine Dard and welcome to Exploits, where we remind you

00:01:19.712 --> 00:01:22.080
That the people who know god

00:01:21.952 --> 00:01:25.376
We'll be strong and carry out exploits.

00:01:25.216 --> 00:01:26.464
The works

00:01:26.272 --> 00:01:27.552
of the Lord.

00:01:28.096 --> 00:01:32.160
Jesus said in the Gospel in John 10:27,

00:01:32.064 --> 00:01:34.368
My shape, hear my voice.

00:01:34.240 --> 00:01:37.152
And I know them and they follow me.

00:01:37.760 --> 00:01:42.432
In today's teaching, I want to observe that we learn to hear God's voice

00:01:42.144 --> 00:01:44.480
Basically four different ways.

00:01:44.608 --> 00:01:48.864
First of all, by reading his word on a daily basis,

00:01:48.672 --> 00:01:54.176
That way we always hear his thoughts and everything that he's recorded for us to know.

00:01:54.368 --> 00:01:59.136
Secondly, we learn to know his voice through familiarity.

00:01:59.168 --> 00:02:02.368
By walking with the Lord day by day.

00:02:02.432 --> 00:02:03.584
Thirdly,

00:02:03.712 --> 00:02:07.136
God speaks to us through godly counsel.

00:02:07.488 --> 00:02:14.560
And fourthly, he speaks to us through our own thoughts and impressions that he gives us.

00:02:15.264 --> 00:02:18.432
Have you learned to discern the Lord's voice?

00:02:19.040 --> 00:02:25.120
The Lord said of his word in no uncertain terms that we are supposed to know his voice.

00:02:25.856 --> 00:02:31.840
For example, when my husband calls me on the telephone, he doesn't have to identify himself.

00:02:31.808 --> 00:02:35.200
Because I know his voice through familiarity.

00:02:35.360 --> 00:02:37.248
He's not a stranger to me.

00:02:37.856 --> 00:02:40.992
But do you know your Lord's voice?

00:02:41.088 --> 00:02:44.960
He's constantly guiding us and always speaking to us, but

00:02:44.992 --> 00:02:46.656
Are we listening?

00:02:47.200 --> 00:02:50.944
He's always broadcasting, but are we picking up?

00:02:50.688 --> 00:02:52.224
His signals.

00:02:52.640 --> 00:02:56.864
As disciples of the Lord, we don't have to stumble in the dark.

00:02:57.216 --> 00:03:01.568
We should be persuaded that we're following his divine will

00:03:01.408 --> 00:03:05.024
And not just the imaginations of our own hearts.

00:03:05.408 --> 00:03:09.344
A great Bible promise is found in Isaiah.

00:03:09.376 --> 00:03:11.744
1 Corinthians chapter 30 and verse 21.

00:03:12.000 --> 00:03:15.904
Where it says your ears you'll hear a word behind you

00:03:15.968 --> 00:03:19.296
Saying this is the way walking in it is

00:03:19.360 --> 00:03:21.184
When you turn to the right

00:03:21.024 --> 00:03:23.200
Or when you turn to the left.

00:03:23.968 --> 00:03:29.056
The direction of the voice from behind is commonly explained.

00:03:28.896 --> 00:03:30.944
by Bible commentators.

00:03:30.912 --> 00:03:35.008
As the practice of shepherds going behind their flocks,

00:03:34.880 --> 00:03:40.416
Are nurses walking behind their patients to observe their emotions?

00:03:40.736 --> 00:03:43.680
Usually, of course, a guy goes in front of us.

00:03:43.424 --> 00:03:51.424
But if we get off track, our backs are turned and consequently the warning voice would be heard from behind.

00:03:52.032 --> 00:03:54.080
Whichever way you interpret it,

00:03:54.016 --> 00:03:56.960
Isaiah 30:21 promises that

00:03:56.768 --> 00:04:01.216
The voice of the Lord will be a faithful guide and monitor.

00:04:02.144 --> 00:04:05.536
Well, what does God's voice actually sound like?

00:04:05.824 --> 00:04:08.352
According to rabbinic tradition,

00:04:08.288 --> 00:04:15.392
God's voice is called a bat-coal in Hebrew, which literally means daughter of a voice.

00:04:15.680 --> 00:04:21.280
The implication is that God's voice is most often a soft voice.

00:04:21.632 --> 00:04:24.064
This rabbinic phrase, "bat called,"

00:04:24.192 --> 00:04:28.640
could also refer to the faint whispers of the Holy Spirit.

00:04:29.344 --> 00:04:34.272
Actually, in the Bible, God's voice has a very wide range of sound.

00:04:34.464 --> 00:04:36.320
At one end of the scale

00:04:36.352 --> 00:04:39.104
In 1 Kings 19,

00:04:39.328 --> 00:04:45.376
The prophet Elijah recognized God by a still small voice.

00:04:45.216 --> 00:04:46.208
But,

00:04:46.176 --> 00:04:49.728
At Mount Sinai, God's voice was frightening.

00:04:49.600 --> 00:04:52.832
It boomed like a trumpet in thunder.

00:04:53.728 --> 00:04:58.304
In the Gospels, a voice from heaven occurs three times.

00:04:58.016 --> 00:04:59.520
when God spoke.

00:04:59.488 --> 00:05:01.760
At the baptism of Jesus?

00:05:01.856 --> 00:05:04.416
At the transfiguration of Jesus,

00:05:04.320 --> 00:05:07.584
and also the night before the Lord's Passion.

00:05:08.320 --> 00:05:12.128
And the Lord himself spoke dramatically to the Apostle Paul

00:05:12.192 --> 00:05:15.648
after he was raised from the dead on the Damascus road.

00:05:15.808 --> 00:05:20.544
The Lord confronted him in a vision by saying, "Saul, Saul!"

00:05:20.416 --> 00:05:22.688
Why are you persecuting me?

00:05:23.552 --> 00:05:27.744
You see, sometimes God audibly calls his servants by name.

00:05:28.096 --> 00:05:31.168
The prophet Samuel, when he was just a child,

00:05:31.104 --> 00:05:34.528
Heard God calling him by name in the night.

00:05:35.552 --> 00:05:39.808
and the great Scottish-American preacher, Peter Marshall,

00:05:40.096 --> 00:05:42.272
In the 20th century, it was

00:05:42.112 --> 00:05:47.616
walking through a bog at night in Scotland and he heard God calling him by name.

00:05:47.648 --> 00:05:49.504
To alert him of

00:05:49.248 --> 00:05:51.040
Impending danger.

00:05:52.000 --> 00:05:57.600
Generally speaking, Jesus has instructed us that we're simply to be like sheep.

00:05:58.080 --> 00:06:01.088
Through familiarity and intimacy,

00:06:00.864 --> 00:06:04.064
Sheep learned to know the voice of their shepherd.

00:06:04.352 --> 00:06:07.136
And so we should know the voice of

00:06:06.880 --> 00:06:09.664
Our Good Shepherd, Jesus the Messiah.

00:06:10.272 --> 00:06:20.320
And Jesus said in John chapter 10 that his sheep hear his voice and follow him because we know his voice and we won't follow the voice of God.

00:06:19.840 --> 00:06:20.512
Always.

00:06:20.544 --> 00:06:22.016
Of a stranger.

00:06:23.520 --> 00:06:29.184
Those who are not his sheep won't heed his voice. They'll be false sheep.

00:06:29.312 --> 00:06:31.584
Enter Lopers in his flock,

00:06:31.360 --> 00:06:34.240
Who one day will be cast out.

00:06:34.304 --> 00:06:41.536
You see, Jesus warned of the future day when his sheep will be separated from the doomed disobedient.

00:06:41.536 --> 00:06:44.576
referred to in the New Testament as goats.

00:06:45.024 --> 00:06:49.024
Well, what side will you be on? Will you be with the sheep in that day?

00:06:48.992 --> 00:06:51.680
Or hopefully you won't be a goat.

00:06:52.448 --> 00:06:55.680
The Good Shepherd is faithful to lead us.

00:06:55.776 --> 00:06:59.136
The famous Psalm 23 in verse 3 declares,

00:06:58.848 --> 00:07:04.096
He leads me in paths of righteousness for his name's sake.

00:07:05.120 --> 00:07:08.160
And so one of the true marks of a disciple

00:07:08.096 --> 00:07:15.584
Is that we'll be a genuine sheep with the ability to recognize the shepherd's voice and to follow him.

00:07:15.872 --> 00:07:18.912
This is an important proof of discipleship.

00:07:19.552 --> 00:07:20.832
of course

00:07:20.544 --> 00:07:28.352
It would be nice and convenient always to hear an audible voice, but that's not the Lord's usual way.

00:07:28.864 --> 00:07:35.360
You see, He wants our spirits to become attuned to His voice, not just our physical ears.

00:07:35.712 --> 00:07:41.600
Most of the time, the Lord uses a still small voice inside of us to guide us.

00:07:41.568 --> 00:07:44.864
Or to let us know when we're not on the right path.

00:07:45.408 --> 00:07:48.288
Some people call it the voice of peace.

00:07:48.672 --> 00:07:53.408
You see, if you don't feel peace about something, definitely don't do it.

00:07:53.952 --> 00:07:58.528
A great spiritual guideline is found in the New Testament in

00:07:58.304 --> 00:08:01.984
Colossians chapter 3 and verse 15, which says,

00:08:02.144 --> 00:08:05.056
Let the peace of God rule.

00:08:05.184 --> 00:08:07.776
Be an umpire in your hearts.

00:08:08.192 --> 00:08:11.808
Many times, God will use people to try to get through to us.

00:08:12.256 --> 00:08:14.976
It might be a word in a sermon or

00:08:14.912 --> 00:08:17.344
"Something a friend says to us."

00:08:17.920 --> 00:08:21.216
God can even speak to us through an unbeliever.

00:08:21.888 --> 00:08:24.352
And sometimes the Lord leads us.

00:08:24.096 --> 00:08:26.496
Through circumstances but

00:08:26.208 --> 00:08:32.288
Godly counsel is a very practical way that God speaks to us often.

00:08:33.216 --> 00:08:38.048
Proverbs 11:14 declares where there's no counsel.

00:08:38.112 --> 00:08:39.648
The people fall.

00:08:39.456 --> 00:08:43.168
But in the multitude of counselors there's safety.

00:08:44.096 --> 00:08:49.472
We can receive godly counsel in the form of an exhortation,

